.TH wmfetchmailmon 1 "@PACKAGE@ @VERSION@"
.SH NAME
wmfetchmailmon \- WindowMaker dockapp (docked application)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.BI "wmfetchmailmon < /var/log/mail.log"
.sp
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B wmfetchmailmon
is a dockapp application rendering the /var/log/mail.log messages
in order to easily understand the fetchmail processing status.

It displays (from top to botom):
.TP
1
the email currently fetched;
.TP
2
the numbers of retrieved messages compared to the total number (for the current address);
.TP
3
a progression bar displaying the previous information;
.TP
4
the size (in bytes) retrieve comapred to the total size (for the current email address);
.TP
5
a progression bar displaying the previous information.

.P
It's possible you have difficulties accessing to /var/log/mail.log (permission
denied).
You will probably have to add your current login to the 'adm' group (or
anything else following your GNU/Linux distribution).

